cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed defense mechanism involves using a large image database for nearest-neighbor search, which is a technique commonly used in image retrieval (cs.MM) and also involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the limitations and vulnerabilities of the proposed defense, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR).
